==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Stank
<hw>Stank</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>estang</ets>, F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧tang</ets>, from L. <ets>stagnum</ets> a pool. Cf.
<er>Stagnate</er>, <er>Tank</er> a cistern.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Water retained by an embankment; a pool of water.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Robert of
Brunne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dam or mound to stop water.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stank hen</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the moor hen;
-- called also <altname>stankie</altname>.</cd> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

